Class MessageSource<Message>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.js4ms.io.channel.MessageSource<Message>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AmtDatagramSource, MulticastPacketSource, UdpDatagramPayloadSource, UdpDatagramSource

    public abstract class MessageSource<Message>
extends Object
    An abstract message source that sends a stream of messages to an OutputChannel.
    Author:
    Greg Bumgardner (gbumgard)

      • start

        public final void start()
                 throws IOException,
                        InterruptedException
        Attempts to start this message source leaving the source in the Started state if successful. Calls the doStart() method which derived classes must implement to perform any actions required to start the source.
        Throws:
        IOException - If an I/O error occurs while starting the source.
        InterruptedException
        IllegalStateException - The message source cannot be started in its current state.

      • stop

        public final void stop()
                throws IOException,
                       InterruptedException
        Attempts to stop this message source leaving the source in the Ready state if successful. Calls the doStop() method which derived classes must implement to perform any actions required to stop the source.
        Throws:
        IOException - If an I/O error occurs while stopping the source.
        InterruptedException - If the calling thread is interrupted while stopping the source.
        IllegalStateException - The message source cannot be stopped in its current state.

      • doStop

      • close

        public final void close()
                 throws InterruptedException
        Attempts to close this message source leaving the source in the Closed state if successful. Calls the doClose() method which derived classes must implement to perform any actions required to stop the source.
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - If the calling thread is interrupted while closing the source.
        IllegalStateException - The message source cannot be closed in its current state.

      • doClose

        protected void doClose()
                throws IOException,
                       InterruptedException
        Performs actions required to close the message source. Default implementation closes the OutputChannel bound to this message source.
        Throws:
        IOException - If an I/O error occurs while closing the source.
        InterruptedException - If the calling thread is interrupted while closing the source.

      • abort

        protected void abort()
              throws InterruptedException
        Called to indicate that another operation has failed. Attempts to close this message source and places the source in the Failed state.
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - If the calling thread is interrupted while closing the source.
